children.strValue: Total Solar Eclipse, November 2012: Images and Video
Want to stay on top of all the space news? Follow
View of the eclipse from Clifton Beach in Queensland, Australia. Credit: Camilla the Rubber Chicken

Here are some images and video from the total solar eclipse from today, November 13/14, 2012 (depending on where you were), which was visible only from the northern part of Australia. The image above comes from
, the mascot of the Solar Dynamics Observatory mission. “Clifton Beach was cheering during the totality and Diamond Ring,” Camilla tweeted.
We’ll be adding more images as they become available.
TV news station in New Zealand:
Screenshot from the webcast feed from Cairns and the Great Barrier Reef, Australia at 20:30 UTC.
Not everyone had good luck. Ian Musgrave from Adelaide, Australia was clouded out. “The sky went eerily dark, and the patch of sun on the sea went out,” he wrote on
. “Afterwards, the cloud went away just as the Sun appeared from behind the Moon. Amazing.”
Screenshot from the Panasonic feed from Fitzroy Island during totality.
Screenshot of NASA’s eclipse webcast feed just the Sun emerged from totality over Palm Cove, Australia. Via Jason Major.
Screenshot of the feed from Fitzroy Island at 20:18 UTC.

podcasts. Nancy is also a NASA/JPL Solar System Ambassador.
